( international ) us flu spread to peak
xinhua news agency report of december 31 from los angeles ( by staff reporter yan liang ) - the centers for disease control and prevention in the united states said on the 31 st that the unseen flu in the united states for more than 30 years has reached its peak , with 45 out of 50 states across the united states having a large - scale flu spread , resulting in a rapid increase in the number of deaths caused by influenza .
according to the statistics of the center as of december 20 , the number of deaths caused by influenza in the united states has set a record high of 7.8 percent of all deaths in the same period .
at least 42 children died of influenza in the united states , and the number of deaths from adults also rose rapidly , but it is not yet accurate at this moment .
experts believe that there are two reasons for the serious spread of influenza in 2003 : first , the flu virus is not a panacea for influenza viruses in previous years , causing an earlier production of vaccines not to be able to effectively prevent the virus . second , the oversupply of flu vaccines in the united states last year and two companies that mainly supply vaccines this year have reduced the production volume to 83 million , resulting in the failure of vaccine supply this year .
despite an average of 36,000 people die of influenza each year in the united states and 1.14 million people are hospitalized due to influenza , it is still very rare to have a certain degree of social panic like this .
william thompson , a us epidemiologist , said that this influenza was the most serious influenza in the united states in the past 30 years and was even earlier than in previous years . many schools had a large - scale flu spread and many places where influenza was injected had lined up .
in the face of such a grim situation , the us ministry of health started the emergency center on 19 december and sent a medical expert team to various states .
