therefore , protecting children from the harm of armed conflicts is an important duty of the international community .
all countries , especially the conflicting parties , should make the greatest efforts to this end .
we are pleased to see that in recent years , the united nations has adopted a series of measures to promote the protection of children in armed conflicts and have achieved positive results .
the security council successively passed four resolutions 1261 ( 1999 ) , 1314 ( 2000 ) , 1379 ( 2001 ) , and 1460 ( 2003 ) , providing an important framework for child protection work .
the un peacekeeping operations in some regions take protecting children as an important task , including the appointment of child protection advisers , and the full consideration of children 's special needs in the process of helping the host countries carry out disarmament , restoration , and returning to society .
some peace accords promoted or participated in by the united nations also contain provisions on the protection of children .
national reconciliation is an important condition for lasting peace and stability in the region after the conflict .
after the conflict stops , if the parties concerned cannot bury old grudges and resolve old grievances , then it will be difficult to truly consolidate the peace situation and even the flames of conflict may ignite again .
in many cases , realizing national reconciliation after the conflict requires the joint efforts of all parties concerned , and at the same time , the support and assistance of the international community , especially the united nations .
for many years , the united nations has played a useful role in helping and promoting the process of national reconciliation among countries after the conflict , and has accumulated a lot of experiences . we believe that , on the whole , to successfully help countries to achieve national reconciliation after the conflict , the united nations must properly handle the following three major relationships :
the relationship between short - term needs and long - term objectives should be taken into consideration .
national reconciliation usually takes a certain process and it is very difficult to achieve it overnight .
different stages should have different focuses .
to promote national reconciliation , it is first necessary to let former combat personnel " bid farewell to weapons " and create a safe environment .
at this stage , it is very important to strive to disarm , resume , and return to society the former combat personnel .
