therefore , we fully support the necessary reforms to the anti - terrorism committee , and we agree with the package of proposals put forward in the report on establishing the anti - terrorism committee executive council , and we hope to resolve these problems as soon as possible , especially the problem of too heavy burdens on the vast numbers of member states .
here , i would like to emphasize that revitalization and reform is a continuous process , that the anti - terrorism committee should maintain policy guidance and guidance for its work , and that all decisions should be made by the plenary session of the anti - terrorism committee .
in recent years , the international community has always paid close attention to the issue of small arms .
this shows that all parties have gradually realized the harm caused to the stability of the regions and countries concerned , the post-war reconstruction , and the social development of the small arms .
fortunately , the united nations has taken a series of effective actions to solve this problem .
in 2001 , the " firearms protocol " attached to the " un convention on cracking down on transnational organized crime " and the " un program of action " for small arms were reached one after another .
this has provided a legal and policy basis for the proper resolution of the issue of small arms , and demonstrated the international community 's determination to crack down on illegal trade of small weapons .
in the past three years , the international community has made great progress in promoting the entry into force of the " firearms protocol " and implementing the " program of action . " in particular , the successful convening of the first annual meeting of the united nations in 2003 on small - scale arms has provided a new driving force for the continued comprehensive and conscientious implementation of the " program of action . "
the resolution 58 / 241 adopted by the un general assembly this year decided to set up a working group to negotiate an international document for the identification and tracking of illegal small arms . this will undoubtedly further promote the international community 's efforts to crack down on the illegal trade of small weapons .
in the same way , the security council has also increasingly attached importance to the issue of small weapons and has conducted special deliberations on many occasions and adopted the chairman 's statement and resolutions .
moreover , in examining a series of issues concerning the protection of civilians , women , and children in the conflicts , the security council has stressed the importance of handling small weapons .
developing the economy and eliminating poverty are the basic premise for achieving sustainable development .
sustainable economic development is the material foundation for environmental protection and all - round social progress .
if we do not solve the problem of existence , we cannot talk about development , much less sustainable development .
promoting economic development and working to eliminate poverty is the only way for developing countries to move toward sustainable development .
if the poverty problem of developing countries is not solved , it will be difficult for developed countries to sustain their development .
rationally using resources and protecting the environment is an inevitable requirement for achieving sustainable development .
development cannot be carried out at the cost of wasting resources and sacrificing the environment .
natural resources are not inexhaustible , but the demand for the development of human society has continually increased . if these relations are not properly handled , this will inevitably lead to the deterioration of the ecological environment and seriously threaten the survival and development of mankind .
only by following the path of a circular economy based on the most effective use of resources and environmental protection can sustainable development be realized .
achieving comprehensive social progress and improving the people 's living standards and quality is the ultimate goal of sustainable development .
