xinhua news agency , ulan bator , january 5 ( reporter lu guodong ) according to a report by the local media on the 5th , by the end of 2003 , the domestic livestock reserve of mongolia was 25.307.8 million , an increase of 16.233 million heads over the same period last year .
it was the first time for mongolia 's livestock to rise after three consecutive years of decline .
last summer , there was plenty of rain , spring and winter , which created favorable conditions for the country 's livestock industry to improve .
as of the end of 2003 , there were 1.556 million camels , 1.953 million horses , 1.784 million cattle , 107.062 million sheep , and 10.634 million goats nationwide .
compared with the same period last year , the number of camels , goats and mivers increased , while the number of horns decreased .
mongolia 's livestock industry was basically privatization in the 1990 s .
however , after privatization , the animal husbandry industry has completely " relied on heaven to eat . "
in 1994 and 1999 , mongolia 's livestock industry flourished for six years due to favorable weather conditions .
by the end of 1999 , mongolia 's domestic livestock had reached a record high of 33.5 million heads .
however , from 2000 to 2002 , mongolia 's livestock industry also suffered setbacks for three consecutive years of heavy snow and summer drought .
at the end of 2002 , the number of domestic animals in mongolia dropped by 9.815 million to 236.845 million .
